        "comment": "Moderate avalanche danger (2nd degree) is declared in the high altitudes of the High Tatras. The danger is concentrated on the northern and shady orientations on the northern side of the mountain. Avalanche release is possible on very steep slopes. Deeper in the profile there is a weak layer of dangerous faceted snow. At altitudes below 1700 m the snow was soaked early last week and therefore hardened and stabilized due to the cooling.",
